Oomlie birds are found within the Kharazi Jungle. Like jungle dwellers, these enormous version of chickens are not aggressive (however using the bull roarer near them will cause them to attack you with the message "A nearby Oomlie bird takes a dislike to the sound you are making" appearing in your chatbox).

They can be killed for their raw oomlie meat, which can be combined with a palm leaf found nearby by shaking Leafy Palm Trees to make wrapped oomlies. Cooking one yields a cooked oomlie wrap.

The Legends' Quest needs to be started in order to kill this monster. However, it can be ranged and then the Telekinetic Grab spell can be used to get the meat before starting Legends Quest.

The Oomlie wrap needs to be made or bought on the Grand Exchange in order to complete the Karamja Tasks.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • They may be based on the Red junglefowl, which are the wild ancestors of chickens in the real world. Oomlie birds are the wild relatives of chickens in RuneScape.
